Light desserts
Is it possible to prepare a refined dessert, bypassing the process of baking the dough? Easy if you resort to the gentle power of Philadelphia Cream Cheeses.

01 Nov 2019, 15:43

Philadelphia cream cheeses are rightfully included in the TOP-20 of the most popular cheeses in the world. The harmonious combination of creamy consistency and universal taste has made them a real asset of world cuisine.
Useful variety
Philadelphia cream cheeses are made from a mixture of milk and cream, and today they are presented with a wide selection of flavors.
The manufacturer constantly keeps abreast of consumer demand and quickly responds to the needs of society. For example, for people with lactose intolerance, a lactose-free version of cream cheese is produced, and for fans of slimness, an easy version of Philadelphia, which contains less fat.
Philadelphia cream cheese is rightfully included in the TOP-20 of the most popular cheeses in the world.
This delicious and healthy cheese treat is a great solution for those who like good nutrition, because it contains balanced protein, essential amino acids and vitamins A, B1, B6, B12, C, PP and K.
Such cheeses are suitable for preparing a wide variety of dishes: cheesecakes and sushi, cream soups and salads, spicy sauces, desserts and fruit cocktails.
Enjoy making delicate desserts by experimenting with various ingredients and creating original recipes.


Philadelphia Cherry Dessert


Product: Philadelphia Original Servings Per Container: 6. Cooking Time: 1 hour 20 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia



Photo: Philadelphia Original

Ingredients:

2 packs of Philadelphia Original (175 g each);
100 g biscotti cookies;
300 g of yogurt with a fat content of 1.5%;
50 g butter;
1 sachet of gelatin;
100 ml of water;
3 tsp lemon juice;
50 g of powdered sugar;
1 tsp vanilla sugar;
125 ml of cherry jam;
1 sprig of fresh lemon balm.

Pour gelatin with 100 ml of cold boiled water and leave for an hour until cooked. Meanwhile, grind the biscotti in a blender to a homogeneous bulk. Cook the ghee, add it to the crushed cookies and mix thoroughly. Evenly lay out the prepared mass in 6 glasses. When pouring gelatin, beat the yogurt with a mixer or whisk. In a separate bowl, prepare the cream by mixing Philadelphia Original cream cheese with lemon juice, icing sugar and vanilla sugar.
Spread cream and cherry jam in glasses in layers. Put prepared portions in the refrigerator for 45 minutes. We take out glasses with dessert and decorate each serving with cherry berries and fresh lemon balm leaves.


Dessert “Fruit mix with oatmeal”


Product: Philadelphia Light Servings Per Container: 2. Cooking Time: 30 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia Light



Photo: Philadelphia Light

Ingredients:

60 g Philadelphia Light;
2 tsp nuts of your choice (pecans, peanuts, walnuts);
10 tbsp. l oatmeal for instant cooking;
80 ml of milk (1.5% fat);
1 apple
300 g of pulp of mango or banana;
130 ml of orange juice (can be replaced to your liking).

Grind nuts, mix with oatmeal, orange juice and milk, put in a food container and put in the refrigerator overnight. Cut 4 thin slices of apple to decorate the dessert. From the remaining part of the apple, mango or banana, we prepare mashed potatoes. Spread oatmeal mixture in layers, chilled, fruit puree, cream cheese Philadelphia Light, decorate with chopped apples and serve.


Dessert "Muesli with fruits and berries"


Product: Philadelphia Lactose Free Servings Per Container: 2. Cooking Time: 10 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia



Photo: Philadelphia Lactose Free

Ingredients:

75 g cream cheese Philadelphia Lactose-free;
2 tbsp. l milk;
60 g muesli with nuts;
150 g of fresh fruit (berries) to choose from.

We distribute a portion of Philadelphia Lactose-Free Cream Cheese into two dessert glasses. Cut the prepared fruit, leave the part for decoration. Mix granola with fruits (berries). Spread this mixture in glasses. Decorate at will.


Dessert "Chocolate pleasure"


Product: Philadelphia Milka Servings Per Container: 4. Cooking Time: 30 minutes.


Photo: Philadelphia Milka



Photo: Philadelphia Milka

Ingredients:

250 g of cream cheese Philadelphia Milka;
1 tbsp. cherry juice with pulp (or to taste);
1 tsp cinnamon
3 tbsp. l milk;
4 Milka Pieguski Cookies (or to taste).

Add cinnamon to the juice and bring to a boil. Cool for 10 minutes and distribute into glasses. Mix Philadelphia Milka with milk and put in glasses. Garnish with cookie slices on top. Cool before serving.
